rithione-containing plant extracts are used in herbal medicine for treatment of [[malaria]]. [[Zinc pyrithione]] is used in commercial [[anti-dandruff shampoo]]s.<ref name= \"O\u2019Donnell2009\">{{Citation |last1= O\u2019Donnell |first1=G. |last2= Poeschl |first2=R. |last3= Zimhony |first3=O.|last4= Gunaratnam |first4=M. |last5= Moreira |first5= J.B.C. |last6= Neidle |first6=S.|last7= Evangelopoulos |first7=D. |last8= Bhakta |first8=S. |last9= Malkinson |first9=J.P.|last10= Boshoff |first10=H.I. |last11= Lenaerts |first11=A. |last12= Gibbons |first12=S. |year=2009 |title=Bioactive pyridine-''N''-oxide disulfides from ''Allium stipitatum'' |journal= J. Nat. Prod. |volume=72 |issue=3 |pages=360\u2013365 |doi=10.1021/np800572r |lastauthoramp=yes |pmc=2765505 |pmid=19093848}}</ref><ref name=Kusterer2010>{{Citation |last1= Kusterer |first1=J. |last2=Vogt |first2=A. |last3= Keusgen |first3=M. |year=2010 |title= Isolation and Identification of a New Cysteine Sulfoxide and Volatile Sulfur Compounds from ''Allium'' Subgenus ''Melanocrommyum'' |journal= J. Agric. Food Chem. |volume=58 |pages=520\u2013526 | doi=10.1021/jf902294c |lastauthoramp=yes |pmid=19919098}}</ref><ref name=Block2010>{{Citation |author=Block, E.|title=Garlic and Other Alliums: The Lore and the Science |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6AB89RHV9ucC&printsec=frontcover|publisher=Royal Society of Chemistry|year=2010|isbn=0-85404-190-7}}</ref><ref name=Block2011>{{Citation |last1=Block |first1=E. |last2=Dane |first2=A.J. |last3=Cody |first3=R.B. |year=2011 |title= Crushing Garlic and Slicing Onions: Detection of Sulfenic Acids and Other Reactive Organosulfur Intermediates from Garlic and Other Alliums Using Direct Analysis in Real Time-Mass Spectrometry (DART-MS) |journal= Phosphorus, Sulfur, Silicon and the Related Elements |volume=186 |issue=5 |pages=1085\u20131093|doi=10.1080/10426507.2010.507728 |lastauthoramp=yes }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Commonscat-inline|Allium stipitatum|''All